    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the theory, but isn't the \"benefit cliff\" just an excuse to keep wages low? it feels like instead of looking at how much people are actually being paid or how automation is changing things, the conversation always just defaults to people being \"lazy\" because of benefits. wouldn't a more nuanced view look at other factors too?",
